   Did You Know ?

   Traffic fatalities decreased by 1 percent from 1997 to 1998 for the
          nation as a whole. Nineteen states showed increases, ranging
          from less than 1 percent to as much as 12 percent.
          (Reference: 1998 Annual Report)

